---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BottomDrawer from '../../components/BottomDrawer.astro';
---

<Layout title="AI Interface Study - Case Study - Nolan">
  <article class="case-study">
    <header class="study-header">
      <div class="study-meta">
        <a href="/" class="back-link">‚Üê Back to Portfolio</a>
        <div class="study-details">
          <span class="study-year">2024</span>
          <span class="study-type">Case Study</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h1>AI Interface Study</h1>
      <p class="study-subtitle">Designing intuitive conversational interfaces for complex AI-powered workflows</p>
    </header>

    <div class="study-content">
      <div class="study-summary">
        <div class="summary-grid">
          <div class="summary-item">
            <h3>Client</h3>
            <p>Enterprise AI Platform</p>
          </div>
          <div class="summary-item">
            <h3>Timeline</h3>
            <p>8 weeks</p>
          </div>
          <div class="summary-item">
            <h3>Role</h3>
            <p>Lead UX Designer</p>
          </div>
          <div class="summary-item">
            <h3>Team</h3>
            <p>3 Designers, 2 Researchers</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="hero-media">
        <img src="https://picsum.photos/900/500?random=110" alt="AI interface design system" />
        <p class="media-caption">Final interface design showcasing conversational AI workflows</p>
      </div>

      <section class="study-section">
        <h2>The Challenge</h2>
        <p>Users were struggling with complex AI model configuration through traditional form-based interfaces. The existing system required deep technical knowledge and resulted in high abandonment rates.</p>
        
        <div class="problem-metrics">
          <div class="metric-card negative">
            <div class="metric-value">73%</div>
            <div class="metric-label">Task Abandonment Rate</div>
          </div>
          <div class="metric-card negative">
            <div class="metric-value">4.2</div>
            <div class="metric-label">Average Support Tickets per User</div>
          </div>
          <div class="metric-card negative">
            <div class="metric-value">45min</div>
            <div class="metric-label">Average Configuration Time</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="study-section">
        <h2>Research & Discovery</h2>
        <p>We conducted interviews with 24 users across different expertise levels to understand their mental models and pain points.</p>
        
        <div class="research-insights">
          <div class="insight-card">
            <div class="insight-icon">üí¨</div>
            <h4>Natural Language Preference</h4>
            <p>Users preferred describing their goals in natural language rather than navigating complex menus</p>
          </div>
          <div class="insight-card">
            <div class="insight-icon">üîÑ</div>
            <h4>Iterative Workflows</h4>
            <p>Configuration is rarely linear - users need to experiment and refine their approach</p>
          </div>
          <div class="insight-card">
            <div class="insight-icon">üë•</div>
            <h4>Collaborative Setup</h4>
            <p>Most configurations involve input from multiple stakeholders with different expertise</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="study-section">
        <h2>Design Process</h2>
        <div class="process-steps">
          <div class="process-step">
            <div class="step-number">01</div>
            <div class="step-content">
              <h4>Conversation Mapping</h4>
              <p>Mapped out natural conversation flows for different configuration scenarios</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="process-step">
            <div class="step-number">02</div>
            <div class="step-content">
              <h4>Prototype Testing</h4>
              <p>Built conversational prototypes and tested with 12 users across 3 iterations</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="process-step">
            <div class="step-number">03</div>
            <div class="step-content">
              <h4>AI Training</h4>
              <p>Collaborated with ML team to train conversation models on real user interactions</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="process-media">
          <img src="https://picsum.photos/800/400?random=111" alt="Design process artifacts" />
          <p class="media-caption">Conversation flow diagrams and user journey maps</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="study-section">
        <h2>Key Design Solutions</h2>
        
        <div class="solution-grid">
          <div class="solution-item">
            <h4>Guided Conversations</h4>
            <p>AI assistant that asks contextual questions to understand user goals and technical requirements</p>
            <div class="solution-demo">
              <div class="chat-interface">
                <div class="chat-message ai">
                  <p>What type of data are you working with for this model?</p>
                </div>
                <div class="chat-message user">
                  <p>Customer support emails that need to be categorized</p>
                </div>
                <div class="chat-message ai">
                  <p>Got it! For email classification, I'd recommend starting with a text classification model. How many categories do you need?</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="solution-item">
            <h4>Visual Configuration</h4>
            <p>Complex settings presented as simple visual choices with AI recommendations</p>
            <div class="config-demo">
              <img src="https://picsum.photos/400/250?random=112" alt="Visual configuration interface" />
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="solution-item">
            <h4>Progressive Disclosure</h4>
            <p>Advanced options revealed contextually based on user choices and experience level</p>
            <div class="disclosure-demo">
              <div class="setting-group">
                <div class="basic-setting">‚úì Automatic optimization</div>
                <div class="advanced-setting">‚öôÔ∏è Manual parameter tuning</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="study-section">
        <h2>Results & Impact</h2>
        <div class="results-grid">
          <div class="result-card positive">
            <div class="result-value">89%</div>
            <div class="result-label">Reduction in Abandonment Rate</div>
            <div class="result-change">‚Üì from 73%</div>
          </div>
          <div class="result-card positive">
            <div class="result-value">12min</div>
            <div class="result-label">Average Configuration Time</div>
            <div class="result-change">‚Üì from 45min</div>
          </div>
          <div class="result-card positive">
            <div class="result-value">92%</div>
            <div class="result-label">User Satisfaction Score</div>
            <div class="result-change">‚Üë from 34%</div>
          </div>
          <div class="result-card positive">
            <div class="result-value">67%</div>
            <div class="result-label">Reduction in Support Tickets</div>
            <div class="result-change">‚Üì from 4.2/user</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <blockquote class="user-quote">
          "This feels like having an AI expert sitting next to me, guiding me through the process. I can finally set up models without feeling lost."
          <cite>‚Äî Senior Data Scientist, Fortune 500 Company</cite>
        </blockquote>
      </section>

      <section class="study-section">
        <h2>Key Learnings</h2>
        <div class="learning-list">
          <div class="learning-item">
            <h4>Context is Everything</h4>
            <p>AI interfaces must understand not just what users want, but why they want it and what constraints they're working within.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="learning-item">
            <h4>Progressive Complexity</h4>
            <p>Start simple and reveal complexity gradually based on user confidence and needs rather than front-loading all options.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="learning-item">
            <h4>Human-AI Collaboration</h4>
            <p>The best interfaces feel like collaborations between human intuition and AI capabilities, not humans serving the AI.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="study-footer">
        <div class="study-tags">
          <span class="tag">AI/ML</span>
          <span class="tag">Conversational UI</span>
          <span class="tag">Enterprise UX</span>
          <span class="tag">User Research</span>
          <span class="tag">Interaction Design</span>
        </div>
        
        <div class="study-nav">
          <a href="/projects/future-design" class="nav-link">‚Üê Previous</a>
          <a href="/blog/typography-research" class="nav-link">Next ‚Üí</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
  
  <BottomDrawer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .case-study {
    min-height: 100vh;
    background: white;
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4rem);
  }

  .study-header {
    margin-bottom: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 4rem);
  }

  .study-meta {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    padding-bottom: 1rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
  }

  .back-link {
    color: #666;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 500;
    transition: color 0.3s ease;
  }

  .back-link:hover {
    color: black;
  }

  .study-details {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .study-year,
  .study-type {
    color: #888;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    padding: 0.3rem 0.8rem;
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
    border-radius: 20px;
  }

  .study-header h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: black;
    line-height: 1.2;
    text-shadow: 
      -0.08em 0 #ff3333,
      0.08em 0 #33ccff,
      -0.12em 0 rgba(255, 51, 51, 0.8),
      0.12em 0 rgba(51, 204, 255, 0.8);
  }

  .study-subtitle {
    font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 2.5vw, 1.4rem);
    color: #666;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .study-content {
    line-height: 1.8;
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.1rem);
  }

  .study-summary {
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .summary-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(150px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
    padding: 2rem;
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.02);
    border-radius: 12px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
  }

  .summary-item h3 {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #666;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .summary-item p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #333;
  }

  .hero-media {
    margin: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem) 0;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .hero-media img,
  .process-media img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: 12px;
    box-shadow: 0 8px 25px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
  }

  .media-caption {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #666;
    font-style: italic;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .study-section {
    margin: 4rem 0;
  }

  .study-section h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.2rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem 0;
    color: black;
  }

  .study-section p {
    color: #444;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .problem-metrics {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .metric-card {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
  }

  .metric-card.negative {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.05), rgba(220, 38, 38, 0.05));
  }

  .metric-value {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: #dc2626;
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .metric-label {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #666;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .research-insights {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
    margin: 3rem 0;
  }

  .insight-card {
    padding: 2rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    border-radius: 12px;
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.01);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .insight-icon {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    display: block;
  }

  .insight-card h4 {
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #333;
  }

  .insight-card p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #666;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .process-steps {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .process-step {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .step-number {
    background: #3366FF;
    color: white;
    width: 40px;
    height: 40px;
    border-radius: 50%;
